<br>
I know how much you love Greenpeace people! Well, Greenpeace have their ships (Rainbow Warrior etc.) in Belfast Port today, but this is slightly different....<br>
<br>
Earlier this year the Ro Ireland put tax on plastic bags. It costs 9p per bag, from any shop in the ROI. They also want to introduce this in the UK, specifically N Ireland.<br>
<br>
The ROI released figures: they claim they have saved 1 billion plastic bags so far, that would otherwise be wasted. These bags take millions of years to decay, and so landfills are pretty pointless.<br>
<br>
The co-op (shopping group) introduced new bags last month, that decay in a matter of month (about 60 months max.) which is much better, and they will introduce them into all stores.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Should there be a tax on bags?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I am not specifying this to any area, but would it help your area if you paid tax on plastic bags. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Would this encourage you to re-use them?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Many of ours just get ripped and then thrown out. L'Clerc (French shopping group) sell good big bags, and encourage you to reuse them. But I don't think it's the law, I just think they are stingy and want more money. <p></p><span class=m><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/uconfound.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CoNfOuNd</A> at: 10/4/02 6:57:47 pm<br></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=45.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003399><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bbbarden.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=swallow>Swallow</A> </span><br><br> <span class=usertitle>Deep Blue Sea<br /><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-2-4.gif /></span><br>  Posts: <b>174</b><br></td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#99CCFF>Posted: 10/5/02 10:03:37 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> -</span><hr size=1> Hmmmm. Yes, I think people would defitnitely think twice about throwing plastic bags away- if there was a price to pay. It seems as though people don't seem to care unless money is involved. They have the attitude- live for today, who cares for tomorrow... and it depresses me. <br>
